## Obsidian CLI (if available)

If `obsidian version` returns output, the Obsidian CLI is registered (Obsidian 1.12+).
On WSL2, `obsidian` is aliased to the Windows `Obsidian.com` binary — the CLI connects to the running Windows Obsidian app, not the Linux AppImage.
When available, **prefer CLI commands** over raw file reads for vault interactions:

| Task | CLI command | Fallback |
|------|------------|---------|
| Search vault | `obsidian search query=<text> format=json` | Grep files |
| Today's daily note | `obsidian daily` (open) / `obsidian daily:read` (read contents) | Read file |
| Get daily note path | `obsidian daily:path` | Derive from date |
| Append to daily note | `obsidian daily:append content=<text>` | Write to file |
| List incomplete tasks | `obsidian tasks todo format=json` | Grep `- [ ]` |
| List completed tasks | `obsidian tasks done format=json` | Grep `- [x]` |
| Find orphaned notes | `obsidian orphans format=json` | Manual link scan |
| Get backlinks | `obsidian backlinks file=<name> format=json` | Grep `[[note]]` |
| Open a note | `obsidian open path=<path>` | N/A |

CLI uses `key=value` syntax for parameters (not `--flag` style). Format is always `format=json`, not `--format json`.
CLI output is structured JSON — parse it to get file paths, scores, and content snippets.
This uses Obsidian's internal search index and costs near-zero tokens vs reading files individually.

